00:22:17.427 --> 00:22:20.260
and don't let anything
touch that knife. got it?

260
00:22:20.260 --> 00:22:21.801
- Got it.
- Okay. good.

261
00:22:21.843 --> 00:22:24.010
Okay. There.

262
00:22:27.926 --> 00:22:31.135
You. hold on to this for me
until I get back.

263
00:22:32.177 --> 00:22:33.676
Superglue?

264
00:22:33.718 --> 00:22:35.926
What are we supposed to do
with Superglue?

265
00:22:35.968 --> 00:22:38.177
Shut up!

266
00:23:07.344 --> 00:23:09.260
- Where do you want this?
- Right there.

267
00:23:09.302 --> 00:23:11.469
Lean back a bit. baby.

268
00:23:18.302 --> 00:23:20.344
This is too much for me.

269
00:23:21.344 --> 00:23:23.093
Oh. no. I don't wanna see this.

270
00:23:23.135 --> 00:23:24.260
Here.

271
00:23:24.302 --> 00:23:26.760
- Here.
- Is that for me?

272
00:23:26.801 --> 00:23:29.801
Yeah. but you're not gonna like it
as much as you think you are.

273
00:23:29.843 --> 00:23:32.093
- Hold him.
- Why does she have...

274
00:23:32.135 --> 00:23:34.093
- Mother...!
- Take it easy. man!

275
00:23:34.135 --> 00:23:37.885
Gotta disinfect the wound.
This gets infected. he'll be hatin' life.

276
00:23:38.801 --> 00:23:39.885
Give me that.

277
00:23:39.927 --> 00:23:43.801
It's gonna do me more good
on the inside right now.

278
00:23:45.427 --> 00:23:47.010
Easy with that.

279
00:23:47.052 --> 00:23:48.843
Give me the Superglue.

280
00:23:56.093 --> 00:23:58.427
Superglue was invented
for surgery. all right?

281
00:23:58.469 --> 00:24:01.509
Superglue and duct tape?
To seal up a wound like that?

282
00:24:01.551 --> 00:24:03.302
It's all we got.

283
00:24:13.801 --> 00:24:16.469
There. That oughtta hold it.

284
00:24:16.509 --> 00:24:18.927
What about the knife?

285
00:24:18.968 --> 00:24:23.260
We'll leave it right where it is
until you get him to an emergency room.

286
00:24:26.010 --> 00:24:28.219
I'm gonna try my cell.

287
00:24:30.635 --> 00:24:31.676
Okay.

288
00:24:31.718 --> 00:24:33.885
Now get the arm.

289
00:24:44.469 --> 00:24:46.052
What else can we do?

290
00:24:46.093 --> 00:24:48.801
- Give me that blanket.
- It's okay. baby.

291
00:24:49.676 --> 00:24:54.302
Keep his arm and the knife immobilized
till you get him to a hospital.

292
00:24:55.135 --> 00:24:57.968
It's gonna be okay.
Thank you.

293
00:24:58.010 --> 00:25:00.177
No problem.

294
00:25:04.219 --> 00:25:05.510
I'd keep him warm.

295
00:25:05.551 --> 00:25:08.177
Come get me if anything changes.

296
00:25:13.843 --> 00:25:19.135
You should know she acts
like more of a slut than she really is.

297
00:25:31.802 --> 00:25:33.843
Joe's gonna be fine.

298
00:25:33.885 --> 00:25:34.927
Matt?

299
00:25:34.968 --> 00:25:38.593
You guys go have fun while I try
and get us the hell out of here.

300
00:25:43.718 --> 00:25:46.344
Hey. you were pretty great in there.

301
00:25:46.802 --> 00:25:48.177
Wanna celebrate?

302
00:25:48.219 --> 00:25:50.010
No. thanks.

303
00:25:50.052 --> 00:25:52.469
Six years without a drop.

304
00:25:54.135 --> 00:25:55.927
So much for the party.

305
00:25:55.968 --> 00:25:57.676
A. A?

306
00:25:57.802 --> 00:26:00.676
Kind of ruins the anonymous part.
but yeah.

307
00:26:00.718 --> 00:26:03.260
and a couple other programs
along the way.

308
00:26:03.302 --> 00:26:06.760
So. what. did you just. like.
party too much in the Army?

309
00:26:06.802 --> 00:26:09.885
Well. that's one way to put it.

310
00:26:10.219 --> 00:26:13.551
Let's just say I let things
get away from me. but I'm better now.

311
00:26:13.593 --> 00:26:16.427
and people say I'm a better man for it.

312
00:26:16.593 --> 00:26:17.927
Are you?

313
00:26:17.968 --> 00:26:20.718
I was pretty damn good
to start with.

314
00:26:20.885 --> 00:26:23.635
Well. I'm Lilly. by the way.

315
00:26:25.177 --> 00:26:28.927
And... you already met
my boyfriend Matt.

316
00:26:28.968 --> 00:26:30.593
That's one way of putting it.

317
00:26:30.635 --> 00:26:32.135
I'm glad to meet <i>you.</i> Lilly.

318
00:26:32.177 --> 00:26:34.385
And I'm Molly.

319
00:26:34.427 --> 00:26:37.551
- No husband. no boyfriend.
- That so?

320
00:26:56.510 --> 00:26:58.052
Oh. my God. Yuck.

321
00:26:58.094 --> 00:26:59.427
What?

322
00:26:59.469 --> 00:27:02.010
There's blood on my shirt.

323
00:27:03.302 --> 00:27:07.219
You're freaking out over this?
You can't even see it.

324
00:27:09.676 --> 00:27:12.344
You know what.
your lip's bleeding.

325
00:27:12.551 --> 00:27:14.302
Here.

326
00:27:16.010 --> 00:27:18.718
God. the moon looks bright out here.

327
00:27:20.927 --> 00:27:22.802
I don't see those lights anymore.

328
00:27:22.843 --> 00:27:24.386
You know. maybe later.

329
00:27:24.427 --> 00:27:26.427
I gotta get my truck out of the road.

330
00:27:26.469 --> 00:27:27.760
Good idea.

331
00:27:27.802 --> 00:27:30.927
We wouldn't want someone
to have a wreck. now. would we?

332
00:27:30.968 --> 00:27:31.968
You know what...

333
00:27:32.010 --> 00:27:33.927
Just don't listen to him. okay?

334
00:27:33.968 --> 00:27:35.802
Come on. let's go.

335
00:27:38.135 --> 00:27:39.635
We need to talk.

336
00:27:39.677 --> 00:27:41.469
You're telling me?

337
00:27:41.510 --> 00:27:45.427
I can understand Molly getting excited
about meeting a new guy. but you?

338
00:27:45.469 --> 00:27:47.344
Jesus. Matt. would you stop?

339
00:27:47.386 --> 00:27:48.427
His name's Richard.

340
00:27:48.469 --> 00:27:51.760
I wouldn't have had to do that
if you weren't thinking with your fists.

341
00:27:51.802 --> 00:27:54.510
Is that it? You're still pissed
'cause I decked him?

342
00:27:54.551 --> 00:27:56.010
Who is that guy. anyway?

343
00:27:56.052 --> 00:27:57.927
Oh. just some guy who saved Joe.

344
00:27:57.968 --> 00:28:01.718
Yeah. well. you should stop
trusting people so much.

345
00:28:01.760 --> 00:28:04.010
Don't walk away from me. Matt.

346
00:28:04.052 --> 00:28:06.968
You're not gonna do this to me again.

347
00:28:07.052 --> 00:28:08.135
Do what?

348
00:28:08.177 --> 00:28:10.593
End another conversation
with your feet.

349
00:28:10.635 --> 00:28:12.635
Give me a break.
You saw the guy's wrists.

350
00:28:12.677 --> 00:28:16.344
It looked like he tried to kill himself
more than once. He's a mental case.

351
00:28:16.386 --> 00:28:18.135
Why are you so paranoid about him?

352
00:28:18.177 --> 00:28:20.760
I'm worried about you. That's all.

353
00:28:20.802 --> 00:28:22.760
Right. right.

354
00:28:22.802 --> 00:28:24.551
What?

355
00:28:24.969 --> 00:28:27.135
You hardly even
pay attention to me anymore.

356
00:28:27.177 --> 00:28:29.718
That's not true.

357
00:28:30.469 --> 00:28:33.510
You spent every weekend for
the past two months working on this.

358
00:28:33.551 --> 00:28:34.885
It's like I don't exist.

359
00:28:34.927 --> 00:28:38.593
I bought the RV for us. so we could
spend more time together.

360
00:28:38.635 --> 00:28:40.469
You got it for you and Joe.

361
00:28:40.510 --> 00:28:42.760
So now your problem's
with my friends?

362
00:28:42.802 --> 00:28:44.593
I didn't say that.

363
00:28:44.635 --> 00:28:45.843
You meant it.

364
00:28:45.885 --> 00:28:48.802
I don't understand why you're
freaked out about a fucking RV.

365
00:28:48.843 --> 00:28:51.593
I'm not freaked out
about the stupid RV.

366
00:28:51.635 --> 00:28:54.010
Then what do you want me to do?

367
00:28:55.760 --> 00:28:56.760
Nothing.

368
00:28:56.802 --> 00:28:58.219
Fine. Can I go back to work?

369
00:28:58.260 --> 00:29:01.927
The sooner we get out of here.
the sooner we can get Joe help.

370
00:29:01.969 --> 00:29:04.261
Yeah. Do whatever you want.

371
00:29:04.302 --> 00:29:06.510
You always do.

372
00:29:13.302 --> 00:29:15.885
It's weird.
Power just went out on me.

373
00:29:15.927 --> 00:29:19.510
Well. the miracle is
it ran for this long.

374
00:29:24.177 --> 00:29:26.718
Either your truck
or Matt's RV better start soon.

375
00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:29.551
I got a massage appointment in Vegas
I am not gonna miss.

376
00:29:29.593 --> 00:29:31.635
We couldn't have that.

377
00:29:38.760 --> 00:29:40.010
That's progress. though.

378
00:29:40.052 --> 00:29:43.219
The radio wouldn't even work
this morning.

379
00:29:43.718 --> 00:29:47.469
Well. looks like
the massage is on me.

380
00:29:50.427 --> 00:29:53.135
Things could be worse.

381
00:29:54.802 --> 00:29:57.843
Well. we better get this thing
out of the road.

382
00:29:59.052 --> 00:30:01.510
- You drive.
- Okay.

383
00:30:24.135 --> 00:30:28.469
So. tell me more about Richard.

384
00:30:28.510 --> 00:30:30.469
Not much to tell. I guess.

385
00:30:30.510 --> 00:30:32.344
I was born and raised in Texas.

386
00:30:32.386 --> 00:30:35.344
played football at high school.

387
00:30:35.386 --> 00:30:37.427
Joined the Army to see the world.

388
00:30:37.469 --> 00:30:39.635
What was it like?

389
00:30:39.718 --> 00:30:41.718
The Army or the world?

390
00:30:43.052 --> 00:30:44.802
Both.

391
00:30:45.135 --> 00:30:47.261
Big and scary.

392
00:30:47.302 --> 00:30:49.635
And lonely.

393
00:30:51.386 --> 00:30:52.760
Were you in that war?

394
00:30:52.802 --> 00:30:54.718
Desert Storm?

395
00:30:55.844 --> 00:30:57.885
Yep. I was there.

396
00:30:58.677 --> 00:31:01.135
Did you ever kill anybody?

397
00:31:02.135 --> 00:31:03.844
Yeah.

398
00:31:06.010 --> 00:31:07.885
I guess that kinda helps explain

399
00:31:07.927 --> 00:31:11.219
some of the bad stuff
that's happened in my life.

400
00:31:12.302 --> 00:31:13.969
It's okay.

401
00:31:14.010 --> 00:31:16.344
You could tell me the bad stuff.

402
00:31:21.344 --> 00:31:23.427
I was a POW.

403
00:31:23.469 --> 00:31:26.261
Spent a couple of weeks
being convinced by the Iraqis

404
00:31:26.302 --> 00:31:29.010
to tell 'em everything I knew.

405
00:31:29.927 --> 00:31:32.552
I was pretty much dead.

406
00:31:34.969 --> 00:31:37.885
They. uh... beat me.

407
00:31:37.927 --> 00:31:40.969
Cut me. shot me. burned me.

408
00:31:41.010 --> 00:31:44.302
They hung me by my wrists
while they did it.

409
00:31:45.261 --> 00:31:46.261
Jesus.

410
00:31:46.302 --> 00:31:50.802
Now. you tell Uncle Sam that.
and he'll say I wasn't even there.

411
00:31:51.302 --> 00:31:55.635
But I got the scars
that say otherwise.

412
00:31:56.428 --> 00:32:00.802
Makes me being prom queen
sound pretty pathetic now.

413
00:32:03.344 --> 00:32:06.136
I don't think you turned out so bad.

414
00:32:08.469 --> 00:32:11.302
Anyway. I healed up pretty good.

415
00:32:11.677 --> 00:32:14.386
I got hooked on morphine doing it.

416
00:32:15.219 --> 00:32:19.010
It's pretty easy
to fall into a bottle after that.

417
00:32:19.677 --> 00:32:23.885
Got my release. spent a couple of years
bouncing around Europe.

418
00:32:24.094 --> 00:32:26.469
But I fought back.

419
00:32:27.136 --> 00:32:28.635
Got a lot of help.

420
00:32:28.677 --> 00:32:31.719
But in the end.
it was all up here.

421
00:32:32.510 --> 00:32:35.344
Just me against myself.

422
00:32:37.052 --> 00:32:38.844
Who won?

423
00:32:40.094 --> 00:32:42.177
I did.

424
00:33:15.344 --> 00:33:17.136
Fuck!

425
00:33:26.052 --> 00:33:27.760
Lilly?

426
00:33:28.386 --> 00:33:31.302
I have been spending
too much time...

427
00:33:34.760 --> 00:33:36.552
Lilly?

428
00:34:02.303 --> 00:34:04.011
Lilly.

429
00:34:11.428 --> 00:34:13.177
Lilly?

430
00:34:32.094 --> 00:34:33.802
Lilly.

431
00:34:36.052 --> 00:34:37.802
Lilly!

432
00:37:38.303 --> 00:37:40.510
How's Joe?

433
00:37:40.844 --> 00:37:43.178
Sleeping. finally.

434
00:37:44.303 --> 00:37:47.136
He was hurting so bad.

435
00:37:53.844 --> 00:37:56.635
It's gonna be fine. June.

436
00:37:57.635 --> 00:38:00.261
I'm sure Matt will have us
on the road soon.

437
00:38:00.261 --> 00:38:03.719
Okay? He didn't mean
for this to happen.

438
00:38:06.428 --> 00:38:08.136
I know.

439
00:38:10.261 --> 00:38:11.470
It's j...

440
00:38:11.510 --> 00:38:13.594
It's just so freakin' frustrating.

441
00:38:13.635 --> 00:38:15.927
knowing that everything
we need is. like.

442
00:38:15.969 --> 00:38:19.635
20 or 30 miles away
where we can't get to it.

443
00:38:23.635 --> 00:38:26.969
I'm gonna go check
and see what's up. okay?

444
00:38:40.053 --> 00:38:43.219
We might as well be
on the fucking moon.

445
00:38:49.345 --> 00:38:51.136
Matt?

446
00:39:13.386 --> 00:39:15.844
- Jesus!
- Sorry.

447
00:39:15.886 --> 00:39:17.594
God!

448
00:39:17.635 --> 00:39:19.345
What are you doing back here?

449
00:39:19.386 --> 00:39:20.927
I was gonna ask the same thing.

450
00:39:20.927 --> 00:39:22.635
I was looking for you.

451
00:39:22.677 --> 00:39:25.011
You found me.

452
00:39:25.510 --> 00:39:27.594
Where the hell were you?

453
00:39:27.636 --> 00:39:31.969
I... thought I saw something.

454
00:39:32.011 --> 00:39:35.261
Look. I'm sorry. I was
a complete jerk to you earlier.

455
00:39:35.303 --> 00:39:37.470
I can understand it if you hate me.

456
00:39:37.510 --> 00:39:39.802
You know I don't hate you.

457
00:39:40.719 --> 00:39:44.844
I was just pissed off and scared.
and I took it out on you.

458
00:39:45.219 --> 00:39:47.011
I know. It's just...

459
00:39:47.011 --> 00:39:50.303
you seem to be
doing that a lot these days.

460
00:39:50.802 --> 00:39:52.844
I'm sorry.

461
00:40:03.552 --> 00:40:05.844
Actually. there's something else.

462
00:40:05.886 --> 00:40:09.094
I know. As soon as we get back.
I'll sell this piece of crap...

463
00:40:09.136 --> 00:40:13.261
and put the money in savings.
- That's not what I was gonna say.

464
00:40:16.178 --> 00:40:18.094
What?

465
00:40:21.552 --> 00:40:24.594
I need to tell you that...

466
00:40:26.094 --> 00:40:27.761
Lilly?

467
00:40:27.802 --> 00:40:29.636
Lilly!

468
00:40:39.303 --> 00:40:41.636
I can't wake up Joe.

469
00:40:44.802 --> 00:40:46.011
Joe.

470
00:40:46.053 --> 00:40:48.303
Joe. wake up. buddy!

471
00:40:58.011 --> 00:40:59.386
Hang in there. pal.

472
00:40:59.386 --> 00:41:01.636
You better go get Richard.

473
00:41:04.094 --> 00:41:07.011
- What's wrong?
- I don't know. but it looks bad.

474
00:41:07.053 --> 00:41:09.303
Let me see.

475
00:41:15.969 --> 00:41:18.136
Come on. Joe.

476
00:41:23.802 --> 00:41:25.345
You said he'd be all right.

477
00:41:25.386 --> 00:41:27.261
He should be.

478
00:41:35.303 --> 00:41:38.220
His breathing's shallow but okay.

479
00:41:38.594 --> 00:41:41.470
Let me check this.

480
00:41:45.136 --> 00:41:47.386
What are you doing?

481
00:41:49.636 --> 00:41:54.053
His abdomen would be hard if there
was internal bleeding. but it seems fine.

482
00:41:54.511 --> 00:41:56.719
Then what's wrong with him?

483
00:41:57.178 --> 00:41:58.761
What the hell is wrong with him?

484
00:41:58.761 --> 00:42:00.802
I don't know.

485
00:42:02.928 --> 00:42:05.386
He might be going into shock.

486
00:42:13.969 --> 00:42:16.386
I need to look at the wound.

487
00:42:17.178 --> 00:42:19.136
Help me get him up.

488
00:42:19.428 --> 00:42:21.136
Gently. gently.

489
00:42:24.470 --> 00:42:26.303
Oh. hell.

490
00:42:30.761 --> 00:42:32.719
Holy shit!

491
00:42:33.136 --> 00:42:36.844
Looks like it did
hit an artery after all.

492
00:42:38.094 --> 00:42:40.594
You said he'd be okay.

493
00:42:44.594 --> 00:42:46.552
What should we do?

494
00:42:47.719 --> 00:42:51.345
We need to get him to a hospital.
that's what we need to do.

495
00:42:52.303 --> 00:42:54.552
You have any luck with this thing?

496
00:42:54.886 --> 00:42:57.386
This thing ain't goin' anywhere.

497
00:42:59.803 --> 00:43:01.511
What about your truck?

498
00:43:01.552 --> 00:43:02.636
No.

499
00:43:02.677 --> 00:43:04.803
Has anyone been able
to get a cell signal?

500
00:43:04.844 --> 00:43:08.095
Cell phones aren't gonna work here.
We're in the middle of nowhere.

501
00:43:08.136 --> 00:43:10.095
Shit.

502
00:43:10.803 --> 00:43:12.803
You gotta try something else.

503
00:43:12.844 --> 00:43:15.552
I can't do anything
without a surgeon.

504
00:43:15.594 --> 00:43:18.095
Fuck. Fuck!

505
00:43:18.136 --> 00:43:21.345
Matt! Matt. what are we
supposed to do?

506
00:43:23.345 --> 00:43:25.386
I'm goin' to get help.

507
00:43:26.136 --> 00:43:28.677
Wait. No! From where?

508
00:43:28.719 --> 00:43:31.761
I don't know. There's gotta be
a gas station or something.

509
00:43:31.803 --> 00:43:33.303
Maybe I can flag down a car.

510
00:43:33.345 --> 00:43:36.053
We're in the middle of nowhere.
You said so yourself.

511
00:43:36.095 --> 00:43:38.803
We can't just stand here
and watch Joe bleed to death.

512
00:43:38.803 --> 00:43:40.803
We gotta try something.

513
00:43:42.178 --> 00:43:44.261
Power lines.

514
00:43:44.886 --> 00:43:46.844
What?

515
00:43:47.594 --> 00:43:49.428
I saw power lines over by my truck.

516
00:43:49.470 --> 00:43:51.636
leadin' over here into the woods.

517
00:43:51.677 --> 00:43:54.095
Yeah. this dirt road's
gotta go somewhere.

518
00:43:54.136 --> 00:43:56.136
Maybe there's a house
over in the woods.

519
00:43:56.178 --> 00:43:57.761
Or there might not be anything.

520
00:43:57.803 --> 00:43:59.261
I've gotta try.

521
00:43:59.303 --> 00:44:01.677
You. you're comin' with me.

522
00:44:01.677 --> 00:44:03.511
I don't think
that will be a good idea.

523
00:44:03.552 --> 00:44:06.552
